<div id="review_64615972" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/64615972" />
    <a title="jo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/210397-jo"><img alt="jo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1237421111p2/210397.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/64615972?book_show_action=true">Jul 22, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="jo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="jo" href="/user/show/210397-jo">jo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/210397-jo?shelf=mystery-thriller">mystery-thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer64615972" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8919218757827682411">i want to say this book is okay, just okay -- good-ish story, good-ish characters, good-ish plot turns, good pace. bosch is a nice protagonist because he&apos;s haunted by demons and it&apos;s nice when your detectives are haunted by demons. it makes them look like the criminals they are pursuing, which is after all the whole premise of the genre. <br/><br/>(i hope i fed the right dog.)<br/><br/>it is not a book that deserves four stars because it&apos;s too improbable. that&apos;s a flaw in a mystery and it bothers me. so many myster</span>
  <span id="freeText8919218757827682411" style="display:none">i want to say this book is okay, just okay -- good-ish story, good-ish characters, good-ish plot turns, good pace. bosch is a nice protagonist because he's haunted by demons and it's nice when your detectives are haunted by demons. it makes them look like the criminals they are pursuing, which is after all the whole premise of the genre. <br /><br />(i hope i fed the right dog.)<br /><br />it is not a book that deserves four stars because it's too improbable. that's a flaw in a mystery and it bothers me. so many mysteries are like that and that's maybe one of the reasons why i don't read mysteries. the main reasons why i don't read mysteries, though, is that you don't get enough of the characters' own psychology, and, generally speaking, there's no growth, no evolution, no learning curve in them. this is not what mysteries are about. they are about evil and perversion and the two faces of criminality.<br /><br />but this book kept me out of the deep waters and close to the shore for a good four days and this alone makes it very dear to me. thank you, michael connelly. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8919218757827682411" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

