<div id="review_2600039147" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2600039147" />
    <a title="Jamie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5367410-jamie"><img alt="Jamie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1474429678p2/5367410.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2600039147?book_show_action=true">Jan 09, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jamie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jamie" href="/user/show/5367410-jamie">Jamie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5367410-jamie?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5367410-jamie?shelf=crime-fiction">crime-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5367410-jamie?shelf=michael-connelly">michael-connelly</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2600039147" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12906172725718948520">This 12th Harry Bosch installment (#17 in the Bosch Universe) did it all for me. I initially was a little worried on whether it had been spoiled, as season one of Bosch heavily took from the plot of Echo Park, but there were so many differences, both minute and massive, that allowed for enough mystery to keep me guessing. Nonetheless, an exceptionally engrossing read. <br/><br/>Rachel Walling in any book is a good book. Kiz Rider and J. Edgar both in a book together again is a good book. Add in potentiall</span>
  <span id="freeText12906172725718948520" style="display:none">This 12th Harry Bosch installment (#17 in the Bosch Universe) did it all for me. I initially was a little worried on whether it had been spoiled, as season one of Bosch heavily took from the plot of Echo Park, but there were so many differences, both minute and massive, that allowed for enough mystery to keep me guessing. Nonetheless, an exceptionally engrossing read. <br /><br />Rachel Walling in any book is a good book. Kiz Rider and J. Edgar both in a book together again is a good book. Add in potentially multiple serial killers, police and political corruption, and the best fictional detective, and it's a damn good book. This cracked my top five Bosch Universe novels.<br /><br />Prototypical Connelly storytelling... taut and deceptively simple prose, quick turns and lots of them, rich character development, and an authentic crime feel. This series just keeps getting better and better.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12906172725718948520" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
